<!--
    Demo Party 04 - Person Requester on case 05 (Resolved General Inquiry)
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the FOURTH of the 8-party demo dataset; it pairs with
    sibling party 05 (Organization/Respondent on the same case 05) to
    demonstrate that the polymorphic UI Policy works correctly on
    General Inquiry case types - one Person row + one Organization row
    on the same case exercises BOTH conditional branches simultaneously.
    Together with parties 01 through 03 and parties 05 through 08, this
    record satisfies AAP Section 0.4.1's seed-data folder requirements
    for `seed-data/parties/`.

    The complete 8-party fixture matrix:

        Party 01 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Party 02 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Party 03 - Person      / Witness    / parent case 04 (Pending GI)
        Party 04 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)  ## THIS FILE
        Party 05 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Party 06 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Party 07 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Party 08 - Person      / Witness    / parent case 09 (Resolved Complaint)

    The 8-party dataset thus exercises:
      * All 2 `party_type` choice values (Person x5, Organization x3) -
        this party contributes the THIRD of the five Person entries.
        The Person branch demonstrates that the conditional UI Policy
        at ../../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml
        correctly shows the <person> reference field and HIDES the
        <organization> reference field when party_type=Person.
      * All 3 example `role_label` values (Requester x3, Respondent x3,
        Witness x2) - this party contributes the SECOND of the three
        Requester entries (the others are party 01 on case 03 and party
        06 on case 08). The Requester role semantically represents the
        external person who FILED the case (per AAP Section 0.7.4 the
        case's requester_name + requester_email fields capture the
        primary external requester; a parallel case_party row with
        role_label=Requester records the same individual as a typed
        party for the polymorphic associations Related List).
      * 5 unique parent cases (03, 04, 05, 08, 09) - this party is
        the FIRST of two parties on case 05 (paired with party 05's
        Organization/Respondent); cases 03, 05, and 08 each have TWO
        parties (Person + Organization) demonstrating the dual-party
        pattern.
      * Both flow paths (General Inquiry: cases 03, 04, 05 / Complaint:
        cases 08, 09) - this party tests the polymorphic Person branch
        on the GENERAL INQUIRY flow's Resolved case; party 06 (Person
        Requester on case 08) tests the same on the Complaint flow's
        In Progress case. Together these two Person/Requester rows on
        active-or-resolving cases prove the Person branch works on
        both flow paths and at multiple lifecycle phases.
      * All 3 demo users as `person` references (manager x2, agent x2,
        viewer x1) - THIS PARTY IS THE SOLE VIEWER ENTRY in the 8-party
