        (parties 01 and 06 on cases 03 and 08) or the demo agent
        (parties 03 and 08 on cases 04 and 09); only this party
        references the demo viewer (case 05). The viewer's appearance
        as a Person/Requester here exercises a critical access-control
        scenario described in Key Insight 1 below.

    Lifecycle position - WHY Person / Requester / parent Resolved
    General Inquiry case is meaningful:
      Per AAP Section 0.5.7 the case_party schema is:
          case        - Reference -> x_[scope]_case (mandatory)
          party_type  - Choice (Person | Organization, mandatory)
          person      - Reference -> sys_user (conditional: required
                        if party_type=Person)
          organization- Reference -> core_company (conditional: required
                        if party_type=Organization)
          role_label  - String(100) (mandatory; example values
                        Requester, Respondent, Witness)

      With party_type=Person, the conditional UI Policy at
      ../../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml
      activates the Person branch:
          - Show + require <person> field (populated below with
            "x_[scope]_demo_viewer")
          - Hide <organization> field (left empty below; the empty
            <organization/> element preserves the dictionary entry's
            existence while signaling no value)

      Case 05 is in Resolved status on the General Inquiry flow per
      ../cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_05.xml. The case was filed by an
      external requester ("Synthetic Requester Five") submitting a
      general inquiry; the demo team's queue accepted the inquiry,
      the manager assigned the demo agent, the agent investigated,
      completed all child tasks (which are now Closed per
      ../tasks/x_[scope]_case_task_demo_04.xml and
      ../tasks/x_[scope]_case_task_demo_05.xml), and resolved the
      case; it now awaits manager review for final closure. The
      <role_label>Requester</role_label> on this party records the
      demo viewer as the EXTERNAL PERSON WHO FILED THE INQUIRY -
      mirroring the case's own requester_name field and providing
      the structured, queryable, polymorphic representation that
      reports and filters can consume. This pattern mirrors party
      01 on case 03 (In Progress GI) and party 06 on case 08
      (In Progress Complaint) but uses a DIFFERENT demo user (the
      viewer rather than the manager) to prove that distinct
      person references work correctly side-by-side in the Update
      Set, AND to demonstrate that even read-only users can be
      typed parties on cases (a crucial subtlety of the ACL model).

      Note: the AAP Section 0.5.7 example role_label values are
      Requester, Respondent, Witness; this party uses Requester to
      complete the Requester triad on the dual-party General Inquiry
      flow path, ensuring the demo dataset exercises the role-label
      diversity across both flow paths and across multiple lifecycle
      phases (case 03 In Progress, case 05 Resolved, case 08 In
      Progress).

