    Key insights (per the agent prompt's "Key Insights" section):
      1. DEMO VIEWER AS REQUESTER ON CASE 05. This is the only seed
         party that uses the demo_viewer user as the `person`
         reference. Per AAP Section 0.5.6 ACL matrix, x_[scope]_
         case_viewer has read-only access on every case_management
         table - the viewer cannot CREATE, WRITE, or DELETE any
         case, task, or party. But the viewer can still BE a typed
         party on a case (specifically, recorded in the person
         column of a case_party row) without that giving them any
         additional permissions on the parent case. This is a
         critical access-control subtlety: BEING a party is purely
         a metadata fact about the case; HAVING access to the case
         is determined by the role+ACL system. The viewer's
         appearance on case 05 as Person/Requester demonstrates
         that the polymorphic association table can store ANY
         user as a party, including users who would otherwise have
         minimal access. (In a real case-management deployment,
         this is the difference between an external requester who
         filed the case and an internal user who has write access
         to it - the requester is recorded as a party but does not
         have write access to the case.)
      2. CASE 05 HAS TWO PARTIES (this + party 05). This dual-party
         arrangement is the canonical exemplar of the polymorphic UI
         Policy on a single case form's Related List. On the case-05
         form, the Related List shows BOTH parties; the polymorphic
         UI Policy renders this party with the person field visible
         (referencing the demo viewer) and party 05 with the
         organization field visible (referencing Synthetic Org Beta)
         - simultaneously, on the same case, in the same Related
         List. This is the General-Inquiry-flow equivalent of the
         case-08 dual-party pattern (parties 06 + 07). Across both
         flow paths, the dual-party pattern demonstrates that the
         polymorphic invariant works correctly when multiple party
         rows on the same case render independently.
      3. `Requester` IS THE AAP SECTION 0.5.7 FIRST EXAMPLE ROLE
         LABEL. The AAP Section 0.5.7 case_party schema lists
         "Requester, Respondent, Witness" as example role_label
         values, with Requester FIRST in the enumeration. This
         party uses Requester to represent the most common and
         idiomatic role on a case_management party - the external
         person who FILED the case. The case's own requester_name
         + requester_email fields capture the same individual at
         the case level; this party records the same individual
         at the structured polymorphic level, allowing reports
         and filters to query across all "Requester" parties
         regardless of party_type or parent case.
      4. NO PII, deterministic sys_ids, `[scope]` preserved. No real
         names, no real email addresses, no real phone numbers, no
         real organizational identifiers. The literal `[scope]`
         placeholder appears verbatim everywhere it is used; the
         PDI substitutes the concrete scope id at apply time.
      5. PAIR WITH PARTY 05. Party 05 (Organization/Respondent on
         case 05, referencing Synthetic Org Beta) and this party
         (Person/Requester on case 05, referencing the demo viewer)
         form the canonical dual-party General Inquiry exemplar at
         the Resolved lifecycle phase. Parties 06 + 07 form the
         dual-party exemplar at the In Progress lifecycle phase on
         the Complaint flow; this 04+05 pair is the General-
         Inquiry-flow analog at a later lifecycle phase. Together
         both pairs prove the polymorphic UI Policy works at both
         lifecycle phases and on both flow paths.
      6. POST-RESOLVE ARCHIVE STATE. Case 05 represents the
         "post-resolve archive" state: all child tasks (04, 05) are
         Closed, both parties (this + party 05) are in place, and
         the case awaits final closure by the manager via the
         validate_closed_transition subflow. THIS PARTY (and its
         sibling party 05) persist through the eventual Resolved
         -> Closed transition unchanged - they are pure metadata,
         not gated by the state machine. Their existence on the
         eventually-Closed case demonstrates that party associations
         survive case closure intact.
      7. PERSON-BRANCH SEMANTIC REFERENCE. Per the source-side
         semantic reference at acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/
         acm-person-plugin/src/main/java/com/armedia/acm/plugins/
         person/model/PersonAssociation.java, ArkCase's
         PersonAssociation entity (mapped to acm_person_assoc) had
         a parentId/parentType pair plus a Person reference and
         person-type/notes/tags fields. The ServiceNow target
         collapses both PersonAssociation AND PersonOrganization
         Association into ONE polymorphic table x_[scope]_case_
         party with party_type as the discriminator and conditional
         person/organization references. This party row exercises
         the Person branch of that collapsed table - the moral
         equivalent of an ArkCase PersonAssociation row with
         personType="Requester" and parentType="CASE_FILE". Per
         the AAP Section 0.5 transformation strategy, the
         polymorphism is implemented via UI Policy rather than
         JPA single-table inheritance, eliminating the need for
         a discriminator column (cm_class_name in ArkCase) and
         using a Choice column (party_type) instead.
-->
<record_update table="x_[scope]_case_party">
    <x_[scope]_case_party action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <case display_value="CASE0000005">CASE0000005</case>
        <organization/>
        <party_type>Person</party_type>
        <person display_value="x_[scope]_demo_viewer">x_[scope]_demo_viewer</person>
        <role_label>Requester</role_label>
        <sys_class_name>x_[scope]_case_party</sys_class_name>
        <sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by>
        <sys_id>947634cfd3a1ef3dc9a59179ba9f515a</sys_id>
        <sys_package display_value="Case Management" source="x_[scope]">x_[scope]</sys_package>
        <sys_scope display_value="Case Management">x_[scope]</sys_scope>
        <sys_update_name>x_[scope]_case_party_demo_04</sys_update_name>
    </x_[scope]_case_party>
</record_update>

